description: Gränges AB engages in the development, production and distribution of aluminium material for heat exchanger applications. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 2,602 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2014-10-10. The company specializes in rolled aluminum products for the manufacture of brazed heat products. The firm directs its offer to original equipment manufacturers (OEM), supporting them in product development. Its key competences include: brazing and processing, mechanical properties, corrosion, and lubrication, chemistry and surfaces. The firm has research and development (R&D) and production facilities in Sweden and China.
naics: Alumina and Aluminum Production and Processing
name: Granges AB
